                    {
                        "id": "pe-3.4_smt",
                        "name": "statement",
                        "prose": "Use lockable physical casings to protect {{ insert: param, pe-3.4_prm_1 }} from unauthorized physical access."
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "pe-3.4_gdn",
                        "name": "guidance",
                        "prose": "The greatest risk from the use of portable devices\u2014such as smart phones, tablets, and notebook computers\u2014is theft. Organizations can employ lockable, physical casings to reduce or eliminate the risk of equipment theft. Such casings come in a variety of sizes, from units that protect a single notebook computer to full cabinets that can protect multiple servers, computers, and peripherals. Lockable physical casings can be used in conjunction with cable locks or lockdown plates to prevent the theft of the locked casing containing the computer equipment."
                    }
